Use the menu to:
	‚Ä¢	Add Kali repos safely
	‚Ä¢	Choose specific categories (wireless, web, exploitation, etc.)
	‚Ä¢	Install entire tool groups or individual tools

install kali-menu

‚∏ª

üßº Uninstalling Katoolin3

If you want to remove it:

sudo katoolin3 --remove

Or just delete the files and remove the Kali repo manually:

sudo rm -rf /opt/katoolin3
sudo rm /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kali.list
sudo apt update


